XSS by Kn0t



There's an XSS vulnerability in your geek-decoding system. This vuln afflicts the page /geek/ungeek.cgi, because it prints variables without clear them from special symbols that can be JavaScript or HTML. This variables are passed by the page /geek/ungeek.html. The user can insert his Geek Code, then this cgi page works with it, returning the meaning. The code is passed from ungeek.html to ungeek.cgi, using a GET request (www.joereiss.net/geek/ungeek.cgi?THAT'S WHAT I'M SAYING) and printing without values. You can do two things to fix this vulnerability:
1) Using the PHP function htmlspecialchars(); to check the possibility of HTML code injection.
2) You can replace the "<" char with a NULL, so you can decode your Geek Code without a risk of HTML injection or Javascript XSS's.

Kn0t "Bubba" Nuanda ~ DUNNO
